column1: #Text=" As for traffic analysis ( finding out who you are talking to rather than finding out what you are telling to whom ) , NSA and GCHQ are known to have access to lots of traffic ( part of this is obtained via the UK-USA agreement ) . Even if one uses strong encryption , it is feasible for them to log the IP addresses and email addresses of all the parties you are connecting to . If necessary , they can even make routers re-route your traffic to their servers . In addition , the European Data Retention directive forces all operators to store such traffic data .
